.TH VIGIL 1 "2026" "vigil 1.0.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vigil \- post-quantum file-integrity monitor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vigil keygen
.RI [ -a\ ALG ]
.RI [ -k\ vigil.key ]
.RI [ -p\ vigil.pub ]
.br
.B vigil baseline
.I path
.RI [ -k\ vigil.key ]
.RI [ -o\ baseline.vgl ]
.RI [ --prev\ OLD.vgl ]
.RI [ --prev-pub\ OLD.pub ]
.RI [ -x\ GLOB\ ... ]
.RI [ --exclude-from\ FILE ]
.RI [ -j\ N ]
.RI [ --one-file-system ]
.RI [ --follow-symlinks ]
.br
.B vigil check
.RI [ path ]
.RI [ -p\ vigil.pub ]
.RI [ -d\ baseline.vgl ]
.RI [ -j\ N ]
.RI [ --quiet ]
.RI [ --json ]
.br
.B vigil watch
.RI [ path ]
.RI [ -p\ vigil.pub ]
.RI [ -d\ baseline.vgl ]
.RI [ --json ]
.RI [ --resweep\ S ]
.RI [ --debounce\ MS ]
.br
.B vigil verify
.RI [ -p\ vigil.pub ]
.RI [ -d\ baseline.vgl ]
.br
.B vigil show
.RI [ -d\ baseline.vgl ]
.RI [ --list ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vigil
records a SHA3-512 fingerprint and the metadata (type, mode, owner, size,
mtime) of every object under a directory tree, and seals the resulting baseline
with a post-quantum ML-DSA (FIPS 204) signature. A later
.B check
re-scans the tree and reports exactly what was added, removed or modified, and
refuses to trust a baseline whose signature does not verify.
.PP
.B vigil watch
adds an inotify watch to the tree and reports drift live until interrupted.
Both
.B check
and
.B watch
accept
.B --json
for machine-readable output (a single object for
.BR check ,
newline-delimited objects for
.BR watch )
and need only the public key, never the secret.
.PP
Paths may be excluded at
.B baseline
time with
.B -x
.IR GLOB " (repeatable) or "
.B --exclude-from
.IR FILE " (one pattern per line). A pattern without a slash matches any path "
component (so
.I *.log
or
.I cache
match anywhere); a pattern with a slash matches the full relative path or any
ancestor prefix. Matched directories are pruned. The exclude set is stored in
the signed baseline, so
.B check
and
.B watch
apply it automatically and identically.
.PP
The secret signing key is encrypted at rest with Argon2id and AES-256-GCM. Set
.B VIGIL_PASSPHRASE
in the environment to operate
.B baseline
and
.B keygen
non-interactively.
.SH EXIT STATUS (check)
.TP
.B 0
Clean: the tree matches the signed baseline.
.TP
.B 2
Drift: one or more objects changed.
.TP
.B 4
Bad signature: the baseline was tampered with or signed by another key.
.TP
.B 1
Usage or runtime error.
.SH AUTHOR
Jean-Francois Lachance-Caumartin.
